## 4\. Detailed Implementation & Code Samples

### 4.1. The Saga Entity (The "Brain")

Centralizes state and cursors. Uses Optimistic Locking.

```java
@Entity
@Table(name = "REVIEW_SAGA")
public class ReviewSaga {
    @Id
    private String reviewId;

    @Enumerated(EnumType.STRING)
    private SagaStatus status; // STARTED, MEMBERS_PENDING, BLOCKS_PENDING, SYNCING, COMPLETED

    // --- State Context ---
    private int totalMembers;
    private int totalBlocks;

    // --- Checkpoints (Cursors) ---
    private int sfMemberOffset = 0;
    private int sfBlockOffset = 0;

    @Version // Crucial for concurrency control
    private Long version;
    
    // Helper to check if sync is fully done
    public boolean isSyncComplete() {
        return sfMemberOffset >= totalMembers && sfBlockOffset >= totalBlocks;
    }
}
```

### 4.2. Step 1: Parallel Block Generation (The "Muscle")

Uses a bounded Thread Pool to handle high volume without crashing the container.

**Configuration:**

```java
@Configuration
@EnableAsync
public class AsyncConfig {
    @Bean(name = "workerExecutor")
    public Executor workerExecutor() {
        ThreadPoolTaskExecutor executor = new ThreadPoolTaskExecutor();
        executor.setCorePoolSize(20); // Limit concurrency
        executor.setMaxPoolSize(40);
        executor.setQueueCapacity(2000);
        executor.setThreadNamePrefix("SagaWorker-");
        executor.initialize();
        return executor;
    }
}
```

**Worker Logic (Idempotent):**

```java
@Service
public class BlockWorker {

    @Async("workerExecutor")
    @Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW)
    public void generateBlocksForMember(String reviewId, String memberId) {
        // 1. Idempotency Check (Restart safety)
        if (blockRepository.existsByReviewAndMember(reviewId, memberId)) {
            return; 
        }

        // 2. Heavy Lifting (API Call + Logic)
        var data = externalApi.fetch(memberId);
        var blocks = createBlocks(data);
        blockRepository.saveAll(blocks);

        // 3. Notify Completion (To trigger Saga progress check)
        events.publishEvent(new MemberProcessingFinishedEvent(reviewId));
    }
}
```

### 4.3. Step 2: The Orchestrator (The "Conductor")

Manages transitions.

```java
@Component
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class SagaOrchestrator {

    private final SagaRepository repository;
    private final ApplicationEventPublisher events;

    // --- Phase 1: Start ---
    @ApplicationModuleListener
    @Transactional
    public void on(ReviewCreatedEvent event) {
        var saga = new ReviewSaga(event.reviewId());
        saga.setStatus(SagaStatus.MEMBERS_PENDING);
        repository.save(saga);
        // Command to Member Module
        events.publishEvent(new GenerateMembersCommand(event.reviewId())); 
    }

    // --- Phase 2: Transition to Sync ---
    @ApplicationModuleListener
    @Transactional
    public void on(AllBlocksGeneratedEvent event) {
        var saga = repository.findById(event.reviewId()).orElseThrow();
        saga.setTotalBlocks(event.totalCount());
        saga.setStatus(SagaStatus.SYNCING);
        repository.save(saga);
        
        // Trigger the Loop
        triggerNextSyncBatch(saga);
    }

    // --- Phase 3: The Sync Loop ---
    @ApplicationModuleListener
    @Transactional
    public void on(SalesforceBatchCompletedEvent event) {
        var saga = repository.findById(event.reviewId()).orElseThrow();
        
        // Update Cursor based on what was just synced
        if (event.type() == DataType.MEMBER) {
            saga.setSfMemberOffset(saga.getSfMemberOffset() + event.count());
        } else {
            saga.setSfBlockOffset(saga.getSfBlockOffset() + event.count());
        }
        
        if (saga.isSyncComplete()) {
            finalizeSaga(saga);
        } else {
            // Re-entrant: Continue the loop in a NEW transaction
            triggerNextSyncBatch(saga);
        }
        repository.save(saga);
    }

    private void triggerNextSyncBatch(ReviewSaga saga) {
        // Priority: Members first, then Blocks
        if (saga.getSfMemberOffset() < saga.getTotalMembers()) {
            events.publishEvent(new SyncBatchCommand(
                saga.getReviewId(), DataType.MEMBER, saga.getSfMemberOffset(), 200));
        } else {
            events.publishEvent(new SyncBatchCommand(
                saga.getReviewId(), DataType.BLOCK, saga.getSfBlockOffset(), 200));
        }
    }
}
```

